<br>
Here's my routine: (shaman outside the group)<br>
<br>
-Reach desired exp spot. (important.. has to be constant pulls)<br>
<br>
-Cast puppy powah pet<br>
<br>
-Buff with group buffs: Khura's, RH (free BP buff), Regen, Acumen, Celerity (dont forget to hit the pet too!), AGI (havent seen a difference with or without it, but it lasts forever and costs almost no mana), Avatar (no primal...gets expensive, but the exp/hour difference is well worth it..pays for itself too with added dead mobs riches)<br>
<br>
-Med to full, park pet, equip shaman epic<br>
<br>
-Pull mobs back to shaman after getting sufficient aggro (wack it a few times)<br>
<br>
-Hotkeys for shaman in order of use: (6) Stand (1) Assist Luchador (2) Turgurs (3) Pet attack (4) Cast epic dot (5) Cann IV (6) Sit<br>
<br>
-Beat the hell out of the mob with warrior get exp<br>
<br>
-Repeat infinately OR until you cant stand hearing the pet barking.. OR you think this is just TOO unfair and you laugh yourself into LD<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
To add spice to this, I have found that a decently equipped warrior (which I am.. not UBER, but decently equipped) could keep himself in berzerker frenzy and tear through mobs like butter! Of course this comes with practice, having guaranteed single pulls (well, no more than 3) and remembering that you need to invite the shaman to torpor yourself in case you get in trouble)<br>
<br>
My record is an AA point in under 2 hours and the most I did before I couldnt stand it anymore is 3.5 points on a saturday<br>
<br>
Having duo'd with a druid, shaman and a cleric.. I can say that by FAR shaman is the BEST partner to have along side a warrior.. unlimited mana, haste, slows, ability to add significant free dmg (thx pet, epic, JBB)<br>
<br>
Hope this info helped! Sorry about the formatting, I'm tired <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
