----------------------------------------------------------<br>
I may have a skewed perception because I use a well equiped 60 druid. With PotG + regen + close to 1k heals I have no problems keeping my warrior propped up. The 34pt DS allows me to pull 3 at a time and kill them in the time it takes to kill 2 mobs pulling singles. I have tried 2 boxing with a 57 shammy and found he was too much work. I tried 2 boxing with various clerics up to an epic'd 60 and even though I could heal much better I was not able to kill as fast.<br>
----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
I also have a well equipped level 60 druid and I simply dont believe your statement that pulling 3 mobs is more efficient than single pulls. If you pull 3 at a time the druid will be very occupied just healing thus not being able to use epic, bracer on all three mobs for max efficiency.<br>
<br>
On the other hand when you single pull you can use epic and bracer for full benifit and mostly have the regen and natures recovery working on warrior.<br>
<br>
Best way to duo with druid as I found it was to pull one mob let warrior tank away and use the druids free dots. While warrior is tanking away with all the regen on warrior as possible the druid pulls another that is root parked, then applies dots once again. Depending on warrior hps he either engages right away once done with first one or uses bandages. I seriuosly think that this method is THE best for warrior/druid combo.<br>
<br>
<br>
On the complixity of the shaman duo'd with warrior I think its just a very simply matter of setting up your macros as Luchador explains.<br>
<br>
Warrior pulls.<br>
<br>
Shaman:<br>
<br>
/sit off<br>
/assist warrior<br>
/cast slow, pause xx<br>
/pet attack, pause xx<br>
/cast canni/dot/whatever<br>
/sit<br>
<br>
JBB macro: (can you map an item for hotkey? cant even remember)<br>
<br>
/cast hotkey x, pause xx<br>
repeat<br>
<br>
And thats just one macro. You could make all sorts for dif. situations.<br>
<br>
So while warrior melee mob you can have a macro for canni dance or you could press your hotkey for jbb whatever.<br>
<br>
Well this is my duo plan and my shaman is being PLed like mad by my druid...cant wait <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubrutalliss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brutalliss</A> at: 8/31/02 12:00:20 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhaass.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 425<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/30/02 3:59:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1219.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:~</span><hr size=1> Man, I wish I had time to PL some AA on my tank with my shaman if you can get an AA point in 2 hours.  Bad part is that I still want AA for the shaman too, so I gots to group :/<br>
