I hear ya Haass!<br>
<br>
The sick thing is, VI in their infinite wisdom in wanting people to group for exp, make exp exponentially harder to get the more people you have in the group. <br>
<br>
Example:<br>
<br>
Since the new UI has come out, I have numerical percentages on all my bars, including my AAXP meter. For each deep blue kill that I get SOLO, I get exactly 1% AAXP points. When grouped with another person, it takes 2 kills to get 1% AAXP points. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Luckily, as a duo you can be twice as effective as one. However, the more people you get in your group, the more efficient you have to be! The only thing that comes close to PLd solo exp (as mentioned above) are INSANE AE groups! Personally I find this rediculous and counter intuitive to how Verant wants us to play this game.<br>
<br>
Hopefully, some of the things they are doing on test (making higher blues/even cons/ yellow yield more exp) will help the situation. Until then, when it comes to exp...I'm gonna go PL myself! /wav <br>
