<br>
Warrior pulls, shaman slows right away (applies epic) then JBB.<br>
<br>
On a one minute fight the shaman can nuke with JBB about 6 times (8 secs x 6 = 48 secs thus allowing about 12 secs for slow and epic).<br>
<br>
On top of that the pet will make some damage (700 a min?) and epic is about 700 a minute also. <br>
<br>
DPM. (rough figures)<br>
<br>
JBB:   1500<br>
Epic:  700<br>
Pet:   700<br>
<br>
Total: 2900<br>
<br>
Warrior will depend solely on weaponry of course but will most likely be doing 2500 a minute.<br>
<br>
So if my calculations is anywhere near the truth your shaman here could actually be outdamaging the warrior! And also mana used is slow for 250 mana. A Troll shaman level 56 with fungi and selfregened is 40 hp pr tic which in one minute is 400 hps. That can almost be converted into the cost of slow.<br>
<br>
If the warrior has fungi and regen on there will be very little healing involved.<br>
<br>
Shaman warrior duo = superior.<br>
<br>
