I also have a well equipped level 60 druid and I simply dont believe your statement that pulling 3 mobs is more efficient than single pulls. If you pull 3 at a time the druid will be very occupied just healing thus not being able to use epic, bracer on all three mobs for max efficiency.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I really have no problem keeping my warrior healed using the pull 3 at a time method. The obvious trick is to not hunt where the mobs hit hard. Here is how I normally PL my warrior with a 60 druid:<br>
<br>
1. Pull 3 with warrior. Usually whack each mob 2 or 3 times then grab another.<br>
2. Run back to druid hit hotkey #1 - assist warrior<br>
3. Hotkey #2 for bracer dot<br>
4. if I bother to have pet up then send him in<br>
5. warrior kills mob #1, switches to next target, usually already down to 75% or less<br>
6. go back to step #3 and repeat, heal as necessary.<br>
7. when killing last mob then hotkey #4 which is /cast snare on the mob. I always fight mobs that assist so they don't run on low health until the last one.<br>
<br>
In a 3 mob pull I will usually heal the warrior twice, once at the end of the first mob, once at the end of the 3rd to top him off.. I have no problem with the druid sitting the majority of the time so mana is very rarely a problem.<br>
<br>
I do have a pocket cleric I am slowly PLing so I can have my own rez bish, gear is more than adequateif you want some ideas for a cleric twink. Magelo is:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=345327">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=345327</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
The PotC earring is a little over the top if you have to buy it, but I was able to trade quest pieces to get all the parts I need for just my labor costs.<br>
