<br>
Bats and spiders are very easy to do. I can easily solo one without a healer. I can take 2 at a time without a healer, but it does require some time to bind up and BP to full, so with a druid healing it's simple. With just the druid + warrior I can keep up with the spawn from SS spider room back to bat 1. These mobs have low HP so bracer DoT + 34pt DS + 11/18 and 12/19 weapons tear through them pretty fast.<br>
<br>
I did try FG once, but at 53, I just didn't have the DPS to kill the shrooms fast enough. I can easily keep the warrior healed, but exp is too slow to bother. I plan to head back that way once the warrior is 58 or higher, but until then I will just exp in SolB and the Hole.<br>
<br>
I will say that this might not be as easy to do if you are not twinked. With druid buffs at 53 my warrior if fighting at 3600hp and 1100AC. With RotG on and a Fungi (its a loaner, I haven't managed to score one yet) the 30 hp/tick regen takes care of a lot of the damage so keeping up with heals is not that hard.<br>
<br>
I don't know why any of you would find this particularly hard to believe. I watch warriors solo multiple mobs in Velks all the time. Any place where a warrior can solo a mob or 2 is the perfect place to duo with a druid bot since the DS cuts fight time in half and keeping up with healing is pretty easy.<br>
<br>
